-- Intesa Sanpaolo Says It's in Due Diligence on Buying Poland's Bank Zachodn
-- Marta Waldoch
-- 2010-07-28T10:38:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-28/intesa-sanpaolo-says-it-s-in-due-diligence-on-buying-poland-s-bank-zachodn.html

          
          
             Intesa Sanpaolo SpA is conducting
due diligence at Poland’s Bank Zachodni WBK SA, a unit that
parent Allied Irish Banks Plc is selling, spokeswoman Francesca
Palermo Patera said today by phone from Milan.  
 Intesa Chief Executive Officer Corrardo Passera said the
due diligence is “going well,” according to Palermo Patera.  
          
          


  


        